<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="156" pageId="2" pageNumber="155" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1910,2007]" box="[199,1436,1982,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1982,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Remarks.</emphasis>
Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[527,622,1982,2007]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
differ from the 
<typeStatus box="[821,919,1982,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="155">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen in having more extensive yellow
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">
markings: entire scutellum, anterior half of first tergite, entire tergites 7–8 and hypopygium are yellow. In contrast, the hind femur is largely black dorsally (
<emphasis box="[636,659,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">vs</emphasis>
reddish yellow in the 
<typeStatus box="[931,1029,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">holotype</typeStatus>
female). The male specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,223,248]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
has an entirely yellow face and a black propodeum. These are the first records of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,248,260,285]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="156">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
